---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Syed Gibran — Rebuilding in Public"
  description="Testing marketing on myself. Writing what happens. For the version of you that felt lost and didn't know where to start."
  canonical="https://syedgibran.com/"
>

  <main id="main-content">

    <!-- HERO — BEAT 1: RECOGNITION -->
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="label"><span class="re">re</span>building in public</p>
        <h1 class="hero__title">
          You are finally here.<br />
          I have been waiting.
        </h1>
        <p class="hero__body">
          I stand where the brightest lose their way. Not to watch, but
          because I lost my way here too. And I found something on the other
          side of the confusion that I could not have found any other way.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CRACK DIVIDER -->
    <div class="container">
      <svg class="crack" viewBox="0 0 720 20" preserveAspectRatio="none" aria-hidden="true">
        <path d="M0 10 L120 10 L145 4 L170 14 L192 7 L220 11 L258 5 L290 12 L320 8 L360 10 L720 10"
          fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.75"
          stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <!-- THE SECRET — BEAT 2 -->
    <section class="secret">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="label">the secret</p>
        <h2 class="secret__title">
          You know something<br />
          you haven't said out loud.
        </h2>
        <div class="secret__body">
          <p>
            The reports you write every month. The content calendar you
            maintain. The likes, the reach, the metrics you present in
            meetings. You already know none of it is the thing itself.
          </p>
          <p>
            You can talk about marketing. You have heard of every framework,
            every tool, every strategy. And the more you learn, the worse it
            gets. Because somewhere underneath all of it lives a thought you
            have never said out loud to anyone.
          </p>
          <p class="secret__whisper">
            "I have not done anything that actually matters."
          </p>
          <p>
            That thought is not a flaw. It is the most honest thing about you.
            And it is exactly why you are here.
          </p>
          <p>Now it lives between us.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CRACK DIVIDER -->
    <div class="container">
      <svg class="crack" viewBox="0 0 720 20" preserveAspectRatio="none" aria-hidden="true">
        <path d="M0 10 L120 10 L145 4 L170 14 L192 7 L220 11 L258 5 L290 12 L320 8 L360 10 L720 10"
          fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.75"
          stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <!-- THE COVENANT — BEAT 3 -->
    <section class="covenant">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="label">the covenant</p>
        <h2 class="covenant__title">
          I killed the version of me<br />
          that is haunting you.
        </h2>
        <div class="covenant__body">
          <p>
            I know your secret because I carried it too. The meetings. The
            reports. The quiet suspicion that none of it was real marketing. I
            sat in that exact place and I know how heavy it gets.
          </p>
          <p>
            So I made a decision. I stopped waiting until I was ready. I
            started with nothing. Zero followers, zero proof, zero certainty.
            I tested marketing on myself, in public, and I wrote down
            everything that happened. The failures. The small discoveries.
            The moments where something finally clicked.
          </p>
          <p>
            Here is what I know now. The person who takes the first step does
            not survive it. Not the performing version. Not the one who
            consumes without building, who understands without testing, who
            waits for the right moment that never comes.
          </p>
          <p>
            That person dies at the threshold. And what rises is stronger at
            the fracture than it ever was before.
          </p>
          <p class="covenant__closing">
            That is the only agreement between us. Take the step. See what
            you become.
          </p>
        </div>
        <a href="/blog/why-i-am-treating-this-website-as-a-marketing-lab/" class="covenant__cta">
          <span>start from the beginning</span>
          <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
            <path d="M3 8h10M9 4l4 4-4 4"
              stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1"
              stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          </svg>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CRACK DIVIDER -->
    <div class="container">
      <svg class="crack" viewBox="0 0 720 20" preserveAspectRatio="none" aria-hidden="true">
        <path d="M0 10 L120 10 L145 4 L170 14 L192 7 L220 11 L258 5 L290 12 L320 8 L360 10 L720 10"
          fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.75"
          stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <!-- BLOG GRID — BEAT 4 -->
    <section class="posts">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="label">the fractures</p>
        <div class="posts__grid">

          <a href="/blog/nothing-on-the-door-that-says-its-mine/" class="post__row">
            <span class="post__number">06</span>
            <span class="post__row-title">Nothing On The Door That Says It's Mine</span>
            <span class="post__date">May 1</span>
          </a>

          <a href="/blog/nothing-was-working-started-paying-attention/" class="post__row">
            <span class="post__number">05</span>
            <span class="post__row-title">Nothing Was Working. So I Started Paying Attention.</span>
            <span class="post__date">Apr 24</span>
          </a>

          <a href="/blog/distribution-doesnt-create-attention/" class="post__row">
            <span class="post__number">04</span>
            <span class="post__row-title">Distribution Doesn't Create Attention</span>
            <span class="post__date">Apr 17</span>
          </a>

          <a href="/blog/what-actually-happens-after-you-go-live/" class="post__row">
            <span class="post__number">03</span>
            <span class="post__row-title">What Actually Happens After You Go Live</span>
            <span class="post__date">Apr 10</span>
          </a>

          <a href="/blog/what-actually-matters-marketing-site/" class="post__row">
            <span class="post__number">02</span>
            <span class="post__row-title">What Actually Matters When Building Your First Marketing Site</span>
            <span class="post__date">Apr 5</span>
          </a>

          <a href="/blog/why-i-am-treating-this-website-as-a-marketing-lab/" class="post__row">
            <span class="post__number">01</span>
            <span class="post__row-title">Why I am Treating This Website as a Marketing Lab</span>
            <span class="post__date">Apr 1</span>
          </a>

        </div>
        <a href="/blog/" class="posts__more">
          <span>follow the rebuild</span>
          <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
            <path d="M3 8h10M9 4l4 4-4 4"
              stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1"
              stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          </svg>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>

</Layout>